  "description": "Conversion of Use Class C3 single family home to 1x 3-bedroom flat on ground floor and change of use to Use Class C4 (HMO-housing in multiple occupation) on first and loft levels with associated amenity, cycle and refuse storage. (Amended Description). \r\rConversion of use class C3 single family home to one flat on ground floor and change of use to use class C4 housing in multiple occupation on first and loft levels\r",
  "site_name": "",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed self contained flat (3-bed) at ground floor, by reason of the insufficient internal area for the single bedroom, would result in a substandard form of accommodation that would be detrimental to the residential amenities of future occupants. In addition to this, the poor quality of accommodation proposed means that a satisfactory compensatory 3+ bedroom unit has not been provided, the proposal is therefore contrary to the National Planning Policy Framework (2021), Policy D6 of the London Plan (2021), Policy CP4 and CP5 of the Enfield Plan Core Strategy (2010), Policies DMD5 and DMD9 of the Development Management Document (2014), and the Technical Housing Standards - Nationally Described Space Standard (2015).",
    "The proposed HMO (at first floor and loft levels) by reason of its inadequate communal kitchen/living space, would represent a substandard and inappropriate form of accommodation which would not be capable of meeting the reasonable needs of occupiers and would be detrimental to the residential amenities of future occupants. The proposal is thereby contrary to Policy D6 of the London Plan, Policy CP4 of the Enfield Plan Core Strategy, Policies DMD5, DMD8 and DMD9 of the Development Management Document, the Mayor of London Housing Supplementary Planning Guidance, The Technical Housing Standards-Nationally Described Space Standards and the guidance contained within the National Planning Policy Framework (2023)."
  ],
